Subject: Re: [T2] 1971 steering box

There is a plastic "gasket" at the base of the column that snaps together so
the column doesn't ground out where it goes through the floor and make the
horn be on all the time. It's right in your Bentley manual. I understand why
you were changing it the way you were, since you were replacing the steering
box anyway, but if you aren't replacing the box there's no reason to touch it.
Much easier from the top. 


Brian



